name: membrane dipeptidase
comment: A membrane-bound, zinc enzyme with broad specificity. Abundant in the kidney cortex. Inhibited by bestatin and cilastatin. Type example of peptidase family M19.

references.title: The purification and properties of a particulate renal dipeptidase.
Metabolism of thienamycin and related carbapenem antibiotics by the renal dipeptidase, dehydropeptidase.
Characterization of the glycosyl-phosphatidylinositol-anchored human renal dipeptidase reveals that it is more extensively glycosylated than the pig enzyme.
